      <title>Chinese social credit system bans millions from taking trains, flying</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANMillions of Chinese citizens have now been banned from traveling by air or train as the government continues to expand its social credit system, the South China Morning Post reports.China is rolling out a social credit system that assigns "personal trustworthiness points" to its citizens as a way to monitoring the public and businesses.Credit history, contract obligation fulfillment, character traits, behavior, preferences and interpersonal relationships are all considered when assigning a credit score, according to Reuters.Trustworthy individuals are to be provided with more access to society, while individuals who are blacklisted will be severely restricted, Reuters reports.An official blacklist released by China's National Enterprise Credit Information Publicity System has also banned more than 3.59 million Chinese businesses in 2018 from accessing financial markets, issuing corporate bonds or taking part in land auctions.About 17.46 million people were not allowed to purchase airline tickets, while 5.47 million weren't allowed to buy tickets for high-speed trains, according to the blacklist.The South China Morning Post cites the blacklist as saying individuals and business were punished for behaviors such as failing to repay loans, false or misleading advertising, or defrauding customers.China plans to fully implement its social credit system by 2020.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Subway riders with social credit score2. Citizens given an individual score based on several factors3. Trustworthy individuals and blacklisted individuals 4. China, airplane and high-speed train5. Chinese flag, financial market icon, corporate bond icon and land auction icon6. Airplane with airline ticket, high speed train with tickets7. Behaviors individuals and companies were punished forVOICEOVER (in English): "China is rolling out a social credit system that assigns 'personal trustworthiness points' to its citizens as a way to monitoring the public and businesses.""According to Reuters, credit history, contract obligation fulfillment, character traits, behavior, preferences and interpersonal relationships are all considered when assigning a credit score.""Trustworthy individuals are to be provided with more access to society, while individuals who are blacklisted will be severely restricted.""The South China Morning Post reports millions of Chinese citizens have now been banned from traveling by air or train as the government continues to expand its social credit system.""An official blacklist released by China's National Enterprise Credit Information Publicity System has also banned more than 3.59 million Chinese businesses in 2018 from accessing financial markets, issuing corporate bonds or taking part in land auctions.""According to the report, about 17.46 million people were not allowed to purchase airline tickets, while 5.47 million weren't allowed to buy tickets for high-speed trains.""The South China Morning Post cites the report as saying individuals and business were punished for behaviors such as failing to repay loans, false or misleading advertising, or defrauding customers."SOURCES: The South China Morning Post, Xinhua, Reuters, National Enterprise Credit Information Publicity System, https://www.scmp.com/economy/china-economy/article/2186606/chinas-social-credit-system-shows-its-teeth-banning-millionshttp://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-11/21/c_137622527.htmhttps://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-society-points/beijing-pioneering-citizens-points-system-critics-brand-orwellian-idUSKCN1NP0FThttp://www.gsxt.gov.cn/%7B3E5A916C593C60E1B5483B5E0A4FDCE914FA6E3A5FB1F40BC0A5FEA5C8A5C0374337433743A59A094966-1550647243824%7D***]]></description>
