      <title>Kim Jong Un sets off on long train trip to Vietnam for Trump summit</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANNorth Korean leader Kim Jong Un set off on a train trip to Vietnam on Saturday to attend a summit with the U.S.According to the BBC, Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump will meet in Hanoi for the second US-North Korea summit, where they are expected to continue denuclearization talks.Russia's TASS news agency, citing a North Korean diplomatic source, said Kim left Pyongyang in an armored train at 5 p.m. on February 23.Reuters reports that two witnesses in Dandong spotted the train crossing from North Korea into China via the Yalu river bridge at around 9:30 p.m.Kim's 21-car train bears a striking resemblance to the armored train his late father Kim Jong Il used to visit allies in China and Russia. According to the Chosun Ilbo, the locomotive contains a conference room, an audience chamber, and bedrooms, and is fitted with satellite phone connections and a flat screen TV.While a plane ride would take only a few hours, the New York Times reports that Kim's journey by rail can take as long as two days.The train is expected to stop at the Vietnamese border station of Dong Dang, where the North Korean leader will disembark and travel the remaining 170 kilometers to Hanoi by car.The summit is scheduled for Wednesday and Thursday, with three sources confirming to Reuters that the preferred location is the Government Guesthouse in central Hanoi.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Donald Trump, Kim Jong Un meeting in Hanoi to discuss denuclearization2. Kim Jong Un's armored train leaving Pyongyang, crossing into China3. 21-car train may be same one used by Kim Jong Il to visit Russia, China4. Facilities, equipment inside the train5. Train route from Pyongyang to Dong Dang, Vietnam6. Kim Jong Un disembarks at Dong Dang station, goes to Hanoi by carVOICEOVER (in English): "According to the BBC, Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump will meet in Hanoi for the second US-North Korea summit, where they are expected to continue denuclearization talks.""Russia's TASS news agency, citing a North Korean diplomatic source, said Kim left Pyongyang in an armored train at 5 p.m. on February 23.""Reuters reports that two witnesses in Dandong spotted the train crossing from North Korea into China via the Yalu river bridge at around 9:30 p.m.""Kim's 21-car train bears a striking resemblance to the armored train his late father Kim Jong Il used to visit allies in China and Russia.""According to the Chosun Ilbo, the locomotive contains a conference room, an audience chamber and bedrooms, and is outfitted with satellite phone connections and a flat screen TV.""While a plane ride only takes a few hours, the New York Times reports that Kim's journey by rail can take as long as two days.""The train is expected to stop at the Vietnamese border station of Dong Dang, where the North Korean leader will disembark and go the remaining 170 kilometers to Hanoi by car."SOURCES: Reuters, New York Times, BBC, Chosun Ilbohttps://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-usa/north-koreas-kim-sets-off-by-train-to-vietnam-for-summit-with-trump-report-idUSKCN1QC053https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/24/world/asia/north-korea-kim-jong-un-china-train.htmlhttps://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-47328334http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2009/11/09/2009110900406.html***]]></description>
