      <title>Central Park Tower to be the tallest residential building in the world</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANReal estate development firm Extell is giving New York City a newly designed tower on West 57th Street.The Guardian reports that a 472 meter high skyscraper called Central Park Tower is being built right next to New York City's Central Park. The tower is designed by architecture firm Adrian Smith + Gordon Gill.A 472 meter high skyscraper called Central Park Tower is being built right next to New York City's Central Park, according to DesignBoom.The building features luxury apartments with glass windows where residents of the tower can get a "million dollar view" of NYC's Central Park, according to Archinect.An exclusive club called the Central Park Club will also be located within the skyscraper, according to a news release by the architectural firm.The club will include amenities such as an 18 meter swimming pool, a resident's billiard's lounge and a sauna and steam room.If everything goes according to plan, Central Park Tower will be the tallest residential building the world once it has opened.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Central Park Tower, Central Park2. Luxury apartment inside the tower3. Central Park Club4. Amenities included in the towerVOICEOVER (in English): "The Guardian reports that a 472 meter high skyscraper called Central Park Tower is being built right next to New York City's Central Park. The tower is designed by architecture firm Adrian Smith + Gordon Gill.""The building features luxury apartments with glass windows where residents of the tower can get a 'million dollar view' of NYC's Central Park, according to Archinect.""An exclusive club called the Central Park Club will also be located within the skyscraper, according to a news release by the architect